<h1>Problem 1803 - 2022 Taiwan TST Round 3, P4 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(\mathcal{X}\) be the collection of all non-empty subsets (not necessarily finite) of the positive integer set \(\mathbb{N}\). Determine all functions \(f: \mathcal{X} \to \mathbb{R}^+\) satisfying the following properties: 
<ul><li>For all \(S\), \(T \in \mathcal{X}\) with \(S\subseteq T\), there holds \(f(T) \le f(S)\).</li><li>For all \(S\), \(T \in \mathcal{X}\), there hold 
\[f(S) + f(T) \le f(S + T),\quad f(S)f(T) = f(S\cdot T),\]
where \(S + T = \{s + t\mid s\in S, t\in T\}\) and \(S \cdot T = \{s\cdot t\mid s\in S, t\in T\}\).</li></ul></p>
